{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840308288,"sessionID":"ses_287adca13ffeZMR47Fm5As7vW1","part":{"id":"prt_d78533f41001xP3bLGFimBsraS","messageID":"msg_d78532dfe001slHi5ey1wAbQdm","sessionID":"ses_287adca13ffeZMR47Fm5As7vW1","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_functions.edit:15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","newString":"# Validate CRD schema\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n```\n\n---\n\n# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native code execution environments for AI agents. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox instance designed for executing code snippets safely. This work extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group with the `CodeInterpreter` type alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Types defined** | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` |\n| **Scheme registration** | Update `register.go` to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in `addKnownTypes` |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation markers |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n| **Generated client surface** | `CodeInterpreterInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers for CodeInterpreter\n- Reconciler/controller logic specific to CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n- Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n- RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n- Multi-version API or conversion webhooks\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` type definitions |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Updated to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in scheme registration |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` (includes CodeInterpreter types) |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`CodeInterpreterPhase`** — enum for lifecycle phases:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype CodeInterpreterPhase string\n\nconst (\n    CodeInterpreterPhasePending   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed    CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n)\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreter`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced,path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase\"\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n\n// CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n// A CodeInterpreter represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets.\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterSpec`** — code execution configuration:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    // Image is the container image to use for the code interpreter sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n\n    // Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n\n    // TimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum execution time (in seconds) for code snippets.\n    // If not specified, a default timeout will be applied.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:default=300\n    TimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n\n    // MaxMemoryMB specifies the maximum memory (in MB) that code execution can use.\n    // This is a soft limit enforced within the sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=64\n    MaxMemoryMB *int32 `json:\"maxMemoryMB,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterStatus`** — execution status and results:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    // Phase represents the current phase of the CodeInterpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n\n    // SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n\n    // LastExecutionTime is the time of the last code execution.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastExecutionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastExecutionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // ExecutionCount is the total number of code executions performed.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n    ExecutionCount int32 `json:\"executionCount,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterList`**:\n\n```go\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n\n// CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\ntype CodeInterpreterList struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Items           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Scheme registration\n\n**Updated `register.go`** — add CodeInterpreter types to scheme:\n\n```go\nfunc addKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n    scheme.AddKnownTypes(\n        SchemeGroupVersion,\n        &AgentRuntime{},\n        &AgentRuntimeList{},\n        &CodeInterpreter{},\n        &CodeInterpreterList{},\n    )\n    metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\ncontroller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nk8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes including CodeInterpreter types)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | ~120 |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Add `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` to `addKnownTypes` |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` (appends to existing) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n| `client-go/` (updated tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList` for CRUD operations |\n| `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` built from these types |\n| Workload Manager controller | Imports types for code interpreter lifecycle reconciliation |\n| Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n| Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition that extends the existing API group. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n- **Compatibility**: Shares the same `v1alpha1` version with `AgentRuntime`, ensuring consistent scheme registration and versioning.\n- **Future**: Adding required fields to `CodeInterpreterSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump and conversion webhook.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Extend AgentRuntime instead of separate CRD\n\n**Approach**: Add a `codeExecution` field to `AgentRuntimeSpec` to support code interpreter use cases within the existing AgentRuntime CRD.\n\n**Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics and configuration requirements (timeout, memory limits) compared to general agent runtimes. Separate CRDs allow independent RBAC, scheduling, and lifecycle management. The client-go library pattern (see spec) explicitly defines separate interfaces for `AgentRuntimes` and `CodeInterpreters`, indicating intentional separation.\n\n### 2. Use v1beta1 version for CodeInterpreter\n\n**Approach**: Define CodeInterpreter in a new API version `v1beta1` while keeping AgentRuntime in `v1alpha1`.\n\n**Rejected because**: Both CRDs are being developed concurrently in the pre-GA phase. Using different versions adds unnecessary complexity for scheme registration, client generation, and version negotiation. A unified `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development.\n\n### 3. Embed full PodSpec in CodeInterpreterSpec\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.PodSpec` directly in `CodeInterpreterSpec` for maximum flexibility.\n\n**Rejected because**: Similar to AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter uses a controlled surface with focused fields (`Image`, `Resources`, `Env`, `TimeoutSeconds`, `MaxMemoryMB`). This simplifies the API and guides users toward code execution best practices without exposing irrelevant PodSpec fields.\n\n### 4. Define CodeInterpreter in separate API group\n\n**Approach**: Create a new API group `code.agentcube.volcano.sh` for the CodeInterpreter CRD.\n\n**Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime share the same runtime concerns (sandbox lifecycle, resource management). Keeping them in the same `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` group simplifies scheme management and aligns with the client-go library structure where both types are accessed through the same `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Condition`, `metav1.Time`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements`, `corev1.EnvVar` |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go (includes CodeInterpreter)\nmake gen-all\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Validate CRD schema\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n\n# Verify compilation includes new types\ngo build ./pkg/apis/...\n\n# Run tests\ngo test ./pkg/apis/...\n```","oldString":"# Validate CRD schema\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n```"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md\n@@ -254,4 +254,288 @@\n \n # Validate CRD schema\n kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n ```\n+\n+---\n+\n+# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n+\n+## Purpose\n+\n+Define the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native code execution environments for AI agents. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox instance designed for executing code snippets safely. This work extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group with the `CodeInterpreter` type alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+### In scope\n+\n+| Item | Detail |\n+|------|--------|\n+| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n+| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n+| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n+| **Types defined** | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` |\n+| **Scheme registration** | Update `register.go` to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in `addKnownTypes` |\n+| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation markers |\n+| **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n+| **Generated client surface** | `CodeInterpreterInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` |\n+\n+### Out of scope\n+\n+- Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers for CodeInterpreter\n+- Reconciler/controller logic specific to CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n+- Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n+- RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n+- Multi-version API or conversion webhooks\n+\n+## Design\n+\n+### File layout\n+\n+| File | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` type definitions |\n+| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Updated to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in scheme registration |\n+| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` (includes CodeInterpreter types) |\n+\n+### Type definitions\n+\n+**`CodeInterpreterPhase`** — enum for lifecycle phases:\n+\n+```go\n+// CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n+// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n+// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n+type CodeInterpreterPhase string\n+\n+const (\n+    CodeInterpreterPhasePending   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n+    CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n+    CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n+    CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed    CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n+)\n+```\n+\n+**`CodeInterpreter`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n+\n+```go\n+// +genclient\n+// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n+// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n+// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n+// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced,path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n+// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase\"\n+// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n+\n+// CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n+// A CodeInterpreter represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets.\n+type CodeInterpreter struct {\n+    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n+    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n+    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n+    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+**`CodeInterpreterSpec`** — code execution configuration:\n+\n+```go\n+// CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n+type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n+    // Image is the container image to use for the code interpreter sandbox.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n+    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n+\n+    // Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // TimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum execution time (in seconds) for code snippets.\n+    // If not specified, a default timeout will be applied.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n+    // +kubebuilder:default=300\n+    TimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // MaxMemoryMB specifies the maximum memory (in MB) that code execution can use.\n+    // This is a soft limit enforced within the sandbox.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=64\n+    MaxMemoryMB *int32 `json:\"maxMemoryMB,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+**`CodeInterpreterStatus`** — execution status and results:\n+\n+```go\n+// CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n+type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n+    // Phase represents the current phase of the CodeInterpreter.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // LastExecutionTime is the time of the last code execution.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    LastExecutionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastExecutionTime,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // ExecutionCount is the total number of code executions performed.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n+    ExecutionCount int32 `json:\"executionCount,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n+\n+    // Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n+    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n+    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+**`CodeInterpreterList`**:\n+\n+```go\n+// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n+// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n+\n+// CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n+type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n+    metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n+    metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n+    Items           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Scheme registration\n+\n+**Updated `register.go`** — add CodeInterpreter types to scheme:\n+\n+```go\n+func addKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n+    scheme.AddKnownTypes(\n+        SchemeGroupVersion,\n+        &AgentRuntime{},\n+        &AgentRuntimeList{},\n+        &CodeInterpreter{},\n+        &CodeInterpreterList{},\n+    )\n+    metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n+    return nil\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Code generation pipeline\n+\n+```\n+controller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n+controller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n+k8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes including CodeInterpreter types)\n+```\n+\n+Invocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n+\n+## Impact analysis\n+\n+### Files created\n+\n+| File | Lines (est.) |\n+|------|-------------|\n+| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | ~120 |\n+\n+### Files modified\n+\n+| File | Change |\n+|------|--------|\n+| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Add `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` to `addKnownTypes` |\n+\n+### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n+\n+| File | Tool |\n+|------|------|\n+| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` (appends to existing) |\n+| `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n+| `client-go/` (updated tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n+\n+### Downstream consumers\n+\n+| Consumer | Dependency |\n+|----------|-----------|\n+| `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList` for CRUD operations |\n+| `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` built from these types |\n+| Workload Manager controller | Imports types for code interpreter lifecycle reconciliation |\n+| Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n+| Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n+\n+### Breaking change risk\n+\n+- **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition that extends the existing API group. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n+- **Compatibility**: Shares the same `v1alpha1` version with `AgentRuntime`, ensuring consistent scheme registration and versioning.\n+- **Future**: Adding required fields to `CodeInterpreterSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump and conversion webhook.\n+\n+## Alternatives considered\n+\n+### 1. Extend AgentRuntime instead of separate CRD\n+\n+**Approach**: Add a `codeExecution` field to `AgentRuntimeSpec` to support code interpreter use cases within the existing AgentRuntime CRD.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics and configuration requirements (timeout, memory limits) compared to general agent runtimes. Separate CRDs allow independent RBAC, scheduling, and lifecycle management. The client-go library pattern (see spec) explicitly defines separate interfaces for `AgentRuntimes` and `CodeInterpreters`, indicating intentional separation.\n+\n+### 2. Use v1beta1 version for CodeInterpreter\n+\n+**Approach**: Define CodeInterpreter in a new API version `v1beta1` while keeping AgentRuntime in `v1alpha1`.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: Both CRDs are being developed concurrently in the pre-GA phase. Using different versions adds unnecessary complexity for scheme registration, client generation, and version negotiation. A unified `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development.\n+\n+### 3. Embed full PodSpec in CodeInterpreterSpec\n+\n+**Approach**: Use `corev1.PodSpec` directly in `CodeInterpreterSpec` for maximum flexibility.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: Similar to AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter uses a controlled surface with focused fields (`Image`, `Resources`, `Env`, `TimeoutSeconds`, `MaxMemoryMB`). This simplifies the API and guides users toward code execution best practices without exposing irrelevant PodSpec fields.\n+\n+### 4. Define CodeInterpreter in separate API group\n+\n+**Approach**: Create a new API group `code.agentcube.volcano.sh` for the CodeInterpreter CRD.\n+\n+**Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime share the same runtime concerns (sandbox lifecycle, resource management). Keeping them in the same `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` group simplifies scheme management and aligns with the client-go library structure where both types are accessed through the same `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`.\n+\n+## Dependencies\n+\n+| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n+|------------|---------|---------|\n+| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Condition`, `metav1.Time`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n+| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements`, `corev1.EnvVar` |\n+| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n+| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n+| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n+\n+## Verification\n+\n+```bash\n+# Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go (includes CodeInterpreter)\n+make gen-all\n+\n+# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\n+make gen-check\n+\n+# Validate CRD schema\n+kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n+\n+# Verify compilation includes new types\n+go build ./pkg/apis/...\n+\n+# Run tests\n+go test ./pkg/apis/...\n+```\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","before":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agent workloads. This work establishes the core API surface — `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, and supporting shared types — that the Workload Manager controller and generated `client-go` library consume.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Types defined** | `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate` |\n| **Scheme registration** | `groupversion_info.go`, `register.go` — `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`, kind constants, `Resource()` helper |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation/default markers |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n| **Generated client surface** | `AgentRuntimeInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `AgentRuntimeLister` |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- `CodeInterpreter` CRD types (separate AR)\n- Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers\n- Reconciler/controller logic\n- Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n- RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | `+groupName` marker, `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Kind constants (`AgentRuntimeKind`, `AgentRuntimeListKind`, `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind`), `SchemeGroupVersion`, `Resource()` helper |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`AgentRuntime`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeSpec`** — sandbox template and session constraints:\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Template *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=podTemplate\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n    SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=sessionTimeout\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=maxSessionDuration\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeStatus`** — condition-based status:\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    // +optional\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeList`**:\n\n```go\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\ntype AgentRuntimeList struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Items           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Shared types** (`TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate`):\n\n```go\ntype ProtocolType string\n\nconst (\n    ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n    ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n)\n\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    // +optional\n    PathPrefix *string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n    // +optional\n    Name *string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Port uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n    Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    // +optional\n    Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    // +optional\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Scheme registration\n\n**`groupversion_info.go`**:\n\n```go\n// +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\npackage v1alpha1\n\nvar (\n    GroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n    SchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n    AddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n)\n```\n\n**`register.go`**:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    AgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n    AgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n    AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n)\n\nvar SchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n\nfunc Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n    return GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n}\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\ncontroller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nk8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | ~25 |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | ~25 |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | ~60 |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~45 |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` |\n| `manifests/charts/base/crds/*.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n| `client-go/` (entire tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` / `AgentRuntimeList` for CRUD operations |\n| `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `AgentRuntimeLister` built from these types |\n| Workload Manager controller | Imports types for sandbox lifecycle reconciliation |\n| Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n| Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n- **Future**: Adding required fields to `AgentRuntimeSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump (`v1alpha1` → `v1alpha2`) and conversion webhook.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Standalone CRD YAML (no Go types)\n\n**Approach**: Write CRD manifests directly as YAML without Go type definitions.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube uses Go controllers (Workload Manager) that require typed Go structs for serialization, validation, and scheme registration. YAML-only CRDs would force manual JSON unmarshaling and lose compile-time type safety.\n\n### 2. Kubebuilder/controller-runtime scaffolding\n\n**Approach**: Use `kubebuilder create api` to scaffold the full controller + CRD project structure.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube's Workload Manager is a Gin-based HTTP service, not a controller-runtime manager. The project uses `controller-gen` for type/code generation only, without the controller-runtime manager scaffolding. Adopting Kubebuilder would introduce an unnecessary runtime dependency and project structure mismatch.\n\n### 3. Multi-version API from day one (`v1alpha1` + `v1beta1`)\n\n**Approach**: Define two API versions simultaneously with a conversion webhook.\n\n**Rejected because**: The project is pre-GA with no existing users. A single `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development. Adding versions and conversion webhooks adds operational complexity without current benefit.\n\n### 4. Embed full `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` instead of custom `SandboxTemplate`\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` directly in `AgentRuntimeSpec` rather than the lighter `SandboxTemplate` wrapper.\n\n**Rejected because**: `SandboxTemplate` provides a controlled surface — optional `labels`/`annotations` maps with a required embedded `corev1.PodSpec` — while keeping the CRD schema focused on what AgentCube manages. Full `PodTemplateSpec` would expose `ObjectMeta` fields that are not relevant to sandbox template configuration.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Duration`, `metav1.Condition`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec` embedded in `SandboxTemplate` |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go\nmake gen-all\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Validate CRD schema\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n```\n","after":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agent workloads. This work establishes the core API surface — `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, and supporting shared types — that the Workload Manager controller and generated `client-go` library consume.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Types defined** | `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate` |\n| **Scheme registration** | `groupversion_info.go`, `register.go` — `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`, kind constants, `Resource()` helper |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation/default markers |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n| **Generated client surface** | `AgentRuntimeInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `AgentRuntimeLister` |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- `CodeInterpreter` CRD types (separate AR)\n- Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers\n- Reconciler/controller logic\n- Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n- RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | `+groupName` marker, `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Kind constants (`AgentRuntimeKind`, `AgentRuntimeListKind`, `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind`), `SchemeGroupVersion`, `Resource()` helper |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate` |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`AgentRuntime`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeSpec`** — sandbox template and session constraints:\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Template *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=podTemplate\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n    SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=sessionTimeout\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=maxSessionDuration\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeStatus`** — condition-based status:\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    // +optional\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeList`**:\n\n```go\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\ntype AgentRuntimeList struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Items           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Shared types** (`TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate`):\n\n```go\ntype ProtocolType string\n\nconst (\n    ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n    ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n)\n\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    // +optional\n    PathPrefix *string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n    // +optional\n    Name *string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Port uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n    Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    // +optional\n    Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    // +optional\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Scheme registration\n\n**`groupversion_info.go`**:\n\n```go\n// +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\npackage v1alpha1\n\nvar (\n    GroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n    SchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n    AddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n)\n```\n\n**`register.go`**:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    AgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n    AgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n    AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n)\n\nvar SchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n\nfunc Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n    return GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n}\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\ncontroller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nk8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | ~25 |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | ~25 |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | ~60 |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~45 |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` |\n| `manifests/charts/base/crds/*.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n| `client-go/` (entire tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` / `AgentRuntimeList` for CRUD operations |\n| `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `AgentRuntimeLister` built from these types |\n| Workload Manager controller | Imports types for sandbox lifecycle reconciliation |\n| Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n| Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n- **Future**: Adding required fields to `AgentRuntimeSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump (`v1alpha1` → `v1alpha2`) and conversion webhook.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Standalone CRD YAML (no Go types)\n\n**Approach**: Write CRD manifests directly as YAML without Go type definitions.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube uses Go controllers (Workload Manager) that require typed Go structs for serialization, validation, and scheme registration. YAML-only CRDs would force manual JSON unmarshaling and lose compile-time type safety.\n\n### 2. Kubebuilder/controller-runtime scaffolding\n\n**Approach**: Use `kubebuilder create api` to scaffold the full controller + CRD project structure.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube's Workload Manager is a Gin-based HTTP service, not a controller-runtime manager. The project uses `controller-gen` for type/code generation only, without the controller-runtime manager scaffolding. Adopting Kubebuilder would introduce an unnecessary runtime dependency and project structure mismatch.\n\n### 3. Multi-version API from day one (`v1alpha1` + `v1beta1`)\n\n**Approach**: Define two API versions simultaneously with a conversion webhook.\n\n**Rejected because**: The project is pre-GA with no existing users. A single `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development. Adding versions and conversion webhooks adds operational complexity without current benefit.\n\n### 4. Embed full `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` instead of custom `SandboxTemplate`\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` directly in `AgentRuntimeSpec` rather than the lighter `SandboxTemplate` wrapper.\n\n**Rejected because**: `SandboxTemplate` provides a controlled surface — optional `labels`/`annotations` maps with a required embedded `corev1.PodSpec` — while keeping the CRD schema focused on what AgentCube manages. Full `PodTemplateSpec` would expose `ObjectMeta` fields that are not relevant to sandbox template configuration.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Duration`, `metav1.Condition`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec` embedded in `SandboxTemplate` |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go\nmake gen-all\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Validate CRD schema\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n```\n\n---\n\n# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native code execution environments for AI agents. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox instance designed for executing code snippets safely. This work extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group with the `CodeInterpreter` type alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n| **Types defined** | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` |\n| **Scheme registration** | Update `register.go` to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in `addKnownTypes` |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation markers |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n| **Generated client surface** | `CodeInterpreterInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers for CodeInterpreter\n- Reconciler/controller logic specific to CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n- Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n- RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n- Multi-version API or conversion webhooks\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` type definitions |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Updated to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in scheme registration |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` (includes CodeInterpreter types) |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`CodeInterpreterPhase`** — enum for lifecycle phases:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype CodeInterpreterPhase string\n\nconst (\n    CodeInterpreterPhasePending   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n    CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed    CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n)\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreter`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n\n```go\n// +genclient\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced,path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase\"\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n\n// CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n// A CodeInterpreter represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets.\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterSpec`** — code execution configuration:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    // Image is the container image to use for the code interpreter sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n    Image string `json:\"image\"`\n\n    // Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n\n    // TimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum execution time (in seconds) for code snippets.\n    // If not specified, a default timeout will be applied.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:default=300\n    TimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n\n    // MaxMemoryMB specifies the maximum memory (in MB) that code execution can use.\n    // This is a soft limit enforced within the sandbox.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=64\n    MaxMemoryMB *int32 `json:\"maxMemoryMB,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterStatus`** — execution status and results:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    // Phase represents the current phase of the CodeInterpreter.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n\n    // SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n\n    // LastExecutionTime is the time of the last code execution.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastExecutionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastExecutionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // ExecutionCount is the total number of code executions performed.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n    ExecutionCount int32 `json:\"executionCount,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterList`**:\n\n```go\n// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n\n// CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\ntype CodeInterpreterList struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Items           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Scheme registration\n\n**Updated `register.go`** — add CodeInterpreter types to scheme:\n\n```go\nfunc addKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n    scheme.AddKnownTypes(\n        SchemeGroupVersion,\n        &AgentRuntime{},\n        &AgentRuntimeList{},\n        &CodeInterpreter{},\n        &CodeInterpreterList{},\n    )\n    metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\ncontroller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nk8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes including CodeInterpreter types)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | ~120 |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Add `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` to `addKnownTypes` |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` (appends to existing) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n| `client-go/` (updated tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList` for CRUD operations |\n| `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` built from these types |\n| Workload Manager controller | Imports types for code interpreter lifecycle reconciliation |\n| Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n| Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition that extends the existing API group. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n- **Compatibility**: Shares the same `v1alpha1` version with `AgentRuntime`, ensuring consistent scheme registration and versioning.\n- **Future**: Adding required fields to `CodeInterpreterSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump and conversion webhook.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Extend AgentRuntime instead of separate CRD\n\n**Approach**: Add a `codeExecution` field to `AgentRuntimeSpec` to support code interpreter use cases within the existing AgentRuntime CRD.\n\n**Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics and configuration requirements (timeout, memory limits) compared to general agent runtimes. Separate CRDs allow independent RBAC, scheduling, and lifecycle management. The client-go library pattern (see spec) explicitly defines separate interfaces for `AgentRuntimes` and `CodeInterpreters`, indicating intentional separation.\n\n### 2. Use v1beta1 version for CodeInterpreter\n\n**Approach**: Define CodeInterpreter in a new API version `v1beta1` while keeping AgentRuntime in `v1alpha1`.\n\n**Rejected because**: Both CRDs are being developed concurrently in the pre-GA phase. Using different versions adds unnecessary complexity for scheme registration, client generation, and version negotiation. A unified `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development.\n\n### 3. Embed full PodSpec in CodeInterpreterSpec\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.PodSpec` directly in `CodeInterpreterSpec` for maximum flexibility.\n\n**Rejected because**: Similar to AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter uses a controlled surface with focused fields (`Image`, `Resources`, `Env`, `TimeoutSeconds`, `MaxMemoryMB`). This simplifies the API and guides users toward code execution best practices without exposing irrelevant PodSpec fields.\n\n### 4. Define CodeInterpreter in separate API group\n\n**Approach**: Create a new API group `code.agentcube.volcano.sh` for the CodeInterpreter CRD.\n\n**Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime share the same runtime concerns (sandbox lifecycle, resource management). Keeping them in the same `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` group simplifies scheme management and aligns with the client-go library structure where both types are accessed through the same `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Condition`, `metav1.Time`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements`, `corev1.EnvVar` |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go (includes CodeInterpreter)\nmake gen-all\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Validate CRD schema\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n\n# Verify compilation includes new types\ngo build ./pkg/apis/...\n\n# Run tests\ngo test ./pkg/apis/...\n```\n","additions":284,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840308266,"end":1775840308283}}}}
